# Galaxy Slurm compute only

Never run parity sweeps, multiprocess tests, LLK pytest sweeps, or craq-sim ttsim workloads on the **login node**.

## From the login node

Submit Slurm jobs only:

- `./scripts/submit-nkapre-parity-ttsim-slurm.sh` — full parity sweep
- `./scripts/submit-nkapre-llk-ttsim-slurm.sh` — LLK weekly + nightly WH
- `./scripts/submit-nkapre-llk-smoke-ttsim-slurm.sh` — quick LLK smoke
- `sbatch scripts/slurm-nkapre-mp-ttsim-job.sh` — multiprocess only

Default Galaxy node: `bh-glx-b06u08` (partition `bh_sc5_B2B9_D12`).

## On compute

All sweep runners call `require_bh_glx_compute()` and exit unless `hostname` matches `bh-glx-*`.

Do not add `ALLOW_LOGIN_RUN` bypasses or run `llk-pytest-sweep.sh` / `setup-llk-ttsim-env.sh` directly on login.
